11#ifndef MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_PACKET_HISTORY_H_
12#define MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_PACKET_HISTORY_H_
13
14#include <deque>
15#include <map>
16#include <memory>
17#include <set>
18#include <vector>
19
20#include "api/function_view.h"
21#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/include/rtp_rtcp_defines.h"
22#include "rtc_base/synchronization/mutex.h"
23#include "rtc_base/thread_annotations.h"
24
25namespace webrtc {
26
27class Clock;
28class RtpPacketToSend;
29
30class RtpPacketHistory {
31 public:
32 enum class StorageMode {
33 kDisabled, // Don't store any packets.
34 kStoreAndCull // Store up to |number_to_store| packets, but try to remove
35 // packets as they time out or as signaled as received.
36 };
37
38 // Snapshot indicating the state of a packet in the history.
39 struct PacketState {
40 PacketState();
41 PacketState(const PacketState&);
42 ~PacketState();
43
44 uint16_t rtp_sequence_number = 0;
45 absl::optional<int64_t> send_time_ms;
46 int64_t capture_time_ms = 0;
47 uint32_t ssrc = 0;
48 size_t packet_size = 0;
49 // Number of times RE-transmitted, ie not including the first transmission.
50 size_t times_retransmitted = 0;
51 bool pending_transmission = false;
52 };
53
54 // Maximum number of packets we ever allow in the history.
55 static constexpr size_t kMaxCapacity = 9600;
56 // Maximum number of entries in prioritized queue of padding packets.
57 static constexpr size_t kMaxPaddingtHistory = 63;
58 // Don't remove packets within max(1000ms, 3x RTT).
59 static constexpr int64_t kMinPacketDurationMs = 1000;
60 static constexpr int kMinPacketDurationRtt = 3;
61 // With kStoreAndCull, always remove packets after 3x max(1000ms, 3x rtt).
62 static constexpr int kPacketCullingDelayFactor = 3;
63
64 RtpPacketHistory(Clock* clock, bool enable_padding_prio);
65
66 RtpPacketHistory() = delete;
67 RtpPacketHistory(const RtpPacketHistory&) = delete;
68 RtpPacketHistory& operator=(const RtpPacketHistory&) = delete;
69
70 ~RtpPacketHistory();
71
72 // Set/get storage mode. Note that setting the state will clear the history,
73 // even if setting the same state as is currently used.
74 void SetStorePacketsStatus(StorageMode mode, size_t number_to_store);
75 StorageMode GetStorageMode() const;
76
77 // Set RTT, used to avoid premature retransmission and to prevent over-writing
78 // a packet in the history before we are reasonably sure it has been received.
79 void SetRtt(int64_t rtt_ms);
80
81 // If |send_time| is set, packet was sent without using pacer, so state will
82 // be set accordingly.
83 void PutRtpPacket(std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet,
84 absl::optional<int64_t> send_time_ms);
85
86 // Gets stored RTP packet corresponding to the input |sequence number|.
87 // Returns nullptr if packet is not found or was (re)sent too recently.
88 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> GetPacketAndSetSendTime(
89 uint16_t sequence_number);
90
91 // Gets stored RTP packet corresponding to the input |sequence number|.
92 // Returns nullptr if packet is not found or was (re)sent too recently.
93 // If a packet copy is returned, it will be marked as pending transmission but
94 // does not update send time, that must be done by MarkPacketAsSent().
95 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> GetPacketAndMarkAsPending(
96 uint16_t sequence_number);
97
98 // In addition to getting packet and marking as sent, this method takes an
99 // encapsulator function that takes a reference to the packet and outputs a
100 // copy that may be wrapped in a container, eg RTX.
101 // If the the encapsulator returns nullptr, the retransmit is aborted and the
102 // packet will not be marked as pending.
103 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> GetPacketAndMarkAsPending(
104 uint16_t sequence_number,
105 rtc::FunctionView<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>(
106 const RtpPacketToSend&)> encapsulate);
107
108 // Updates the send time for the given packet and increments the transmission
109 // counter. Marks the packet as no longer being in the pacer queue.
110 void MarkPacketAsSent(uint16_t sequence_number);
111
112 // Similar to GetPacketAndSetSendTime(), but only returns a snapshot of the
113 // current state for packet, and never updates internal state.
114 absl::optional<PacketState> GetPacketState(uint16_t sequence_number) const;
115
116 // Get the packet (if any) from the history, that is deemed most likely to
117 // the remote side. This is calculated from heuristics such as packet age
118 // and times retransmitted. Updated the send time of the packet, so is not
119 // a const method.
120 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> GetPayloadPaddingPacket();
121
122 // Same as GetPayloadPaddingPacket(void), but adds an encapsulation
123 // that can be used for instance to encapsulate the packet in an RTX
124 // container, or to abort getting the packet if the function returns
125 // nullptr.
126 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> GetPayloadPaddingPacket(
127 rtc::FunctionView<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>(
128 const RtpPacketToSend&)> encapsulate);
129
130 // Cull packets that have been acknowledged as received by the remote end.
131 void CullAcknowledgedPackets(rtc::ArrayView<const uint16_t> sequence_numbers);
132
133 // Mark packet as queued for transmission. This will prevent premature
134 // removal or duplicate retransmissions in the pacer queue.
135 // Returns true if status was set, false if packet was not found.
136 bool SetPendingTransmission(uint16_t sequence_number);
137
138 // Remove all pending packets from the history, but keep storage mode and
139 // capacity.
140 void Clear();
141
142 private:
143 struct MoreUseful;
144 class StoredPacket;
145 using PacketPrioritySet = std::set<StoredPacket*, MoreUseful>;
146
147 class StoredPacket {
148 public:
149 StoredPacket(std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet,
150 absl::optional<int64_t> send_time_ms,
151 uint64_t insert_order);
152 StoredPacket(StoredPacket&&);
153 StoredPacket& operator=(StoredPacket&&);
154 ~StoredPacket();
155
156 uint64_t insert_order() const { return insert_order_; }
157 size_t times_retransmitted() const { return times_retransmitted_; }
158 void IncrementTimesRetransmitted(PacketPrioritySet* priority_set);
159
160 // The time of last transmission, including retransmissions.
161 absl::optional<int64_t> send_time_ms_;
162
163 // The actual packet.
164 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet_;
165
166 // True if the packet is currently in the pacer queue pending transmission.
167 bool pending_transmission_;
168
169 private:
170 // Unique number per StoredPacket, incremented by one for each added
171 // packet. Used to sort on insert order.
172 uint64_t insert_order_;
173
174 // Number of times RE-transmitted, ie excluding the first transmission.
175 size_t times_retransmitted_;
176 };
177 struct MoreUseful {
178 bool operator()(StoredPacket* lhs, StoredPacket* rhs) const;
179 };
180
181 // Helper method used by GetPacketAndSetSendTime() and GetPacketState() to
182 // check if packet has too recently been sent.
183 bool VerifyRtt(const StoredPacket& packet, int64_t now_ms) const
184 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(lock_);
185 void Reset() RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(lock_);
186 void CullOldPackets(int64_t now_ms) RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(lock_);
187 // Removes the packet from the history, and context/mapping that has been
188 // stored. Returns the RTP packet instance contained within the StoredPacket.
189 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> RemovePacket(int packet_index)
190 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(lock_);
191 int GetPacketIndex(uint16_t sequence_number) const
192 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(lock_);
193 StoredPacket* GetStoredPacket(uint16_t sequence_number)
194 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(lock_);
195 static PacketState StoredPacketToPacketState(
196 const StoredPacket& stored_packet);
197
198 Clock* const clock_;
199 const bool enable_padding_prio_;
200 mutable Mutex lock_;
201 size_t number_to_store_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
202 StorageMode mode_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
203 int64_t rtt_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
204
205 // Queue of stored packets, ordered by sequence number, with older packets in
206 // the front and new packets being added to the back. Note that there may be
207 // wrap-arounds so the back may have a lower sequence number.
208 // Packets may also be removed out-of-order, in which case there will be
209 // instances of StoredPacket with |packet_| set to nullptr. The first and last
210 // entry in the queue will however always be populated.
211 std::deque<StoredPacket> packet_history_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
212
213 // Total number of packets with inserted.
214 uint64_t packets_inserted_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
215 // Objects from |packet_history_| ordered by "most likely to be useful", used
216 // in GetPayloadPaddingPacket().
217 PacketPrioritySet padding_priority_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
218};
219} // namespace webrtc
220#endif // MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_PACKET_HISTORY_H_
221
